    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "For the C core repo, having some proto files in a submodule might be complicated from the point of view of different build systems (they might expect proto files in specific locations in our repo and it's easier to build proto files that are directly checked into the main repo). One solution that might work for C core repo:\r\n- add all the shared protos to grpc/grpc-proto\r\n- have copies of shared protoc directly in grpc/grpc\r\n- add a sanity test to check that protos in grpc/grpc are the same as the reference ones in grpc/grpc-proto (easy to add to our existing sanity suite)."
  },
